main event: An unidentified object was observed in the sky in Palacios, Texas on February 16, 1959, for a duration of 10 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting involved two objects,The course of the sighting was described as possibly the light from the star Arcturus,Sketched observations included details of the object's height above the horizon,The observer was age 75 and unemployed with technical pharmaceuticals training,The object appeared to have a distinct glow and changed in size before becoming invisible.
witness description: A 75-year-old unemployed male with technical pharmaceuticals training.
